{{Quote|This one is an Alliance Medal of Honor. Guess they'll give it to anyone now a days they're so desperate. It makes them feel invulnerable, also makes them an easy target.|A retired [[Imperial officer/Legends|Imperial officer]]|<ref name="sony">{{SonyCite|url=content.jsp?page=Friday%20Feature:%20Medals|text=Friday Feature: Medals}}</ref>}}
The '''Alliance Medal of Honor''' was a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] military decoration awarded to those who performed above and beyond the call of duty while serving in, or with, the [[Alliance Military/Legends|Alliance Military]]. The award was a silver badge emblazoned with the red phoenix of the Alliance beneath an etching of an [[X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing starfighter]]. It was attached to a red ribbon encrusted with various gems.<ref name="SWGTCG" /> The Galactic Empire had a similar award named [[Medal of Honor (Imperial)/Legends|Imperial Medal of Honor]].<ref name="sony" />

By the time of the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] pilot shot down a Rebel pilot above [[Dantooine/Legends|Dantooine]] and stole his Alliance Medal of Honor.<ref name="sony" /> In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> one such medal was awarded to a [[Spacer/Legends|spacer]] alongside several Rebel supporters who assassinated an Imperial officer aboard a Rebel [[CR90 corvette/Legends|Corellian corvette]] captured by the Empire before he could used the ship against civilian targets.<ref name="SWG:CC">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=heroic|Corellian Corvette}}</ref> The same year, another Alliance Medal of Honor was awarded to an [[Ace/Legends|ace]] pilot involved in the destruction of the Imperial [[Corvette/Legends|corvette]] ''[[Star Ravager]]'' in the [[Kessel system/Legends|Kessel system]].<ref name="SWG:JtL">''[[Star Wars Galaxies: Jump to Lightspeed]]''</ref>

